  "text": "What a night in the World Cup! Quarter-final, 10 July 2026, Los Angeles — and Spain broke Belgian hearts with a late winner to reach the semi-finals. Two of Europe's most talented squads traded blows in Los Angeles, with a semi-final against France waiting for the winner.\n\n30' — Fabián Ruiz buried it, 1–0! 41' — Charles De Ketelaere lashed it home, 1–1! 88' — Mikel Merino made no mistake, 2–1!\n\nFabián Ruiz turned in an early opener, slotting home a rebound to give Spain control. Charles De Ketelaere levelled for Belgium, keeping his own fine tournament going and setting up a tense finale. The decisive moment arrived in the 88th minute: Merino pounced on a shot from Cubarsí that goalkeeper Senne Lammens spilled into his path, and Spain were through. Spain's blend of youth and control looked increasingly like that of a side built to go all the way.\n\nYou could feel the tension crackle around the ground with every attack.\n\nThis is knockout football at its rawest — win, or fly home.\n\nThe neutrals were on their feet; nobody in the building sat still.\n\nGolden Boot, glory, the lot — it was all on the line out there.\n\nFULL-TIME: Spain 2–1 Belgium! Spain march on, Belgium head home heartbroken — and here's the beautiful part: every goal, every minute you just heard is locked on-chain and verified by TxLINE. No hot air, no guesswork, just receipts. What. A. Game!",
